I"<p>With college football less than 100 days away, here is a look at just how far 250 of the nationâ€™s top incoming prospects have to travel to get to their chosen colleges.</p>

<p>The prospect data come courtesy of <a href="https://n.rivals.com/prospect_rankings/rivals250/2016">Rivals</a>, while I obtained school location data from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_NCAA_Division_I_FBS_football_programs">Wikipedia</a>.</p>

<p>The small blue dots represent hometowns and the larger black stars represent colleges and universities.</p>

<p>R Code is included below while my data wrangling code is posted to my <a href="https://github.com/jskaza/jskaza.github.io/tree/source/content/supps/Recruiting/recruits_data.ipynb">GitHub</a>.</p>

